ggest%20names%20than%20it's%20ever%20been.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20top%2010%20stocks%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fs%26amp%3Bp_500%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ES%26amp%3BP%20500%3C%2Fa%3E%20now%20make%20up%20about%2040%25%20of%20the%20benchmark%20index%2C%20an%20all-time%20high%2C%20according%20to%20Morningstar%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221431%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22market%20concentration%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68b1eecf194a2d49b8af76f8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22805%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EMorningstar%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-tech-stocks-spending-ai-capex-hyperscalers-alphabet-meta-amazon-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EHigh%20concentration%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20any%20portfolio%20can%20be%20risky%20because%2C%20while%20it%20can%20mean%20more%20upside%20potential%20if%20the%20select%20few%20names%20do%20well%2C%20it%20also%20comes%20along%20with%20more%20downside%20risk%20if%20things%20go%20awry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20particular%20episode%20of%20concentration%20may%20be%20especially%20risky%20for%20the%20broader%20market%20because%20the%20top%20eight%20companies%20are%20technology%20or%20technology-like%20firms%2C%20said%20Dominic%20Pappalardo%2C%20chief%20multi-asset%20strategist%20at%20Morningstar%20Wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20vast%20majority%20of%20the%20top%2010%20are%20all%20very%20likely%20to%20move%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20Pappalardo%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BSo%20if%20you%20have%20one%20or%20two%20of%20those%20tech%20names%20come%20out%20with%2C%20let's%20say%2C%20weak%20earnings%20next%20quarter%2C%20it's%20likely%20that%20all%20eight%20of%20those%20are%20going%20to%20move%20downward%20and%20sell%20off%20simultaneously%2C%20which%20is%20going%20to%20have%20an%20outsized%20impact%20on%20the%20level%20of%20that%20index.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20go%20back%20to%20a%20period%20like%20April%2C%20where%20we%20had%20the%20post-Liberation%20Day%20sell-off%2C%20those%20names%20also%20led%20the%20market%20downward.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPappalardo%20said%20it%20wouldn't%20be%20surprising%20to%20see%20a%20pullback%20in%20the%20market%20in%20the%20near%20future%2C%20given%20that%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20is%20near%20record%20highs.%20And%20while%20he%20said%20he%20doesn't%20believe%20a%20recession%20is%20imminent%2C%20he%20also%20unpacked%20a%20few%20potential%20threats%20to%20the%20rally%20that%20could%20start%20to%20emerge%20in%20the%20months%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20one%2C%20the%20labor%20market%20could%20soften%20further.%20The%20most%20recent%20jobs%20report%20showed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjuly-jobs-report-unemployment-rate-employment-federal-reserve-interest-rates-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehistorically%20weak%20employment%20growth%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20May%2C%20June%2C%20and%20July.%20Investors%20will%20get%20their%20next%20insight%20into%20the%20health%20of%20the%20labor%20market%20from%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20in%20the%20September%205%20payrolls%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lackluster%20job%20growth%20appeared%20to%20be%20enough%20to%20convince%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20to%20resume%20its%20rate%20cuts%20in%20September%2C%20which%20investors%20have%20cheered%20on.%20But%20Pappalardo%20said%20that%20rate%20cuts%20may%20only%20boost%20stocks%20if%20the%20labor%20market%20holds%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20Fed%20is%20only%20cutting%20rates%20because%20they%20think%20the%20economy%20is%20weakening%20to%20a%20point%20where%20they%20have%20to%20step%20in%20and%20support%20it%20longer-term%2C%20that's%20not%20a%20great%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESomething%20else%20that%20could%20create%20issues%20for%20investors%20is%20inflation%2C%20he%20said.%20It%20has%20already%20proven%20sticky%2C%20with%20the%20Consumer%20Price%20Index%20up%202.7%25%20year-over-year%20in%20July.%20Core%20Personal%20Consumption%20Expenditures%2C%20the%20Fed's%20preferred%20inflation%20measure%2C%20was%20up%202.9%25%20in%20July.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETariffs%20have%20fed%20into%20that%20data%2C%20and%20are%20still%20working%20their%20way%20into%20the%20economy%2C%20he%20said.%20If%20inflation%20remains%20elevated%2C%20the%20Fed%20is%20more%20likely%20to%20keep%20rates%20high%2C%20slowing%20economic%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20question%20tariffs%20have%20increased%20prices%20for%20businesses%20and%20consumers%2C%20it's%20just%20a%20simple%20fact%2C%26quot%3B%20Pappalardo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20things%20that%20are%20lining%20up%20to%20be%20concerning.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20diversify%20your%20portfolio%20further%20if%20you're%20overweight%20tech%20stocks%2C%20Pappalardo%20suggested%20adding%20exposure%20to%20international%20stocks%2C%20small-cap%20stocks%2C%20and%20the%20healthcare%20sector%20because%20of%20its%20earnings%20prospects%20and%20low%20valuations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-crash-more-concentrated-than-ever-ai-tech-morningstar-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1756546502000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68b1ee36194a2d49b8af76c6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-crash-more-concentrated-than-ever-ai-tech-morningstar-2025-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20particular%20episode%20of%20concentration%20may%20be%20especially%20risky%20for%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20because%20the%20top%208%20companies%20are%20tech-related%20firms.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22wedwards%40businessinsider.com%20(William%20Edwards)