0is%20usually%20mounded%20around%20the%20base%20of%20a%20plant%20to%20get%20large%20rhizomes.%20At%20first%2C%20Kanchan%20says%20she%20did%20not%20know%20the%20right%20time%20to%20earth%20up%20the%20plant.%20She%20later%20learned%20that%20it%20was%20done%20a%20month%20after%20planting%20the%20crop.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20sowing%20period%20is%20between%20June%20and%20July%2C%20the%20crop%20is%20ready%20for%20harvest%20by%20February-end.%20She%20points%20out%20that%20it%20is%20very%20important%20to%20keep%20in%20mind%20the%20kind%20of%20soil%20used%20for%20cultivation.%20%E2%80%9COur%20region%20is%20famous%20for%20black%20soil%20that%20is%20suitable%20for%20wheat%20cultivation.%20However%2C%20a%20well-drained%20sandy%20loam%20soil%20rich%20in%20humus%20content%20works%20well%20for%20growing%20turmeric%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20informs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAlso%2C%20black%20soil%20is%20soft%20when%20wet%20but%20forms%20hard%20blocks%20when%20it%20gets%20dry.%20So%2C%20we%20need%20a%20sandy%20loamy%20solid%20that%20is%20well-drained.%20In%20our%20district%2C%20only%20a%20few%20blocks%20including%20our%20Kesla%20block%20have%20such%20soil%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20about%20the%20fertilisers%20and%20pesticides%20required%20for%20boosting%20turmeric%20growth%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20only%20use%20cow%20dung%20and%20%3Cem%3Ejeevamrut%20%3C%2Fem%3E(liquid%20organic%20manure)%20to%20boost%20the%20fertility%20of%20the%20soil.%20Besides%2C%20as%20turmeric%20in%20itself%20is%20antiseptic%20and%20herbal%2C%20there%20are%20fewer%20chances%20of%20pest%20attack.%20Even%20if%20pests%20attack%20the%20crop%2C%20we%20use%20Trichoderma%20biopesticides%20to%20control%20the%20attack%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20she%20wanted%20to%20be%20careful%20of%20growing%20a%20new%20crop%2C%20Kanchan%20sowed%20and%20used%20only%20an%20acre%20of%20land%20to%20sow%20eight%20quintals%20of%20turmeric%20root.%20After%20eight%20months%